Defendant Clarence J Beal in court with Attorney Marcella De Peters.  Defendant Clarence J Beal in custody.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Matter here for Sentencing.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by:  Milwaukee Police Detective Eric Draeger, Melissa H., Pat H., and Jason S.

AS TO COUNT #4:  The Court imposed the following sentence:  The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be FIVE (5) years.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for THREE (3) years with credit for 219 days time served.  Defendant shall serve TWO (2) years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  

AS TO COUNT #6:  The Court imposed the following sentence:  The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be FIVE (5) years CONSECUTIVE to count #4.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for THREE (3) years.  Defendant shall serve TWO (2) years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  

AS TO COUNT #7:  The Court ordered the Defendant to serve SIX (6) months CONSECUTIVE to count #6 in the House of Correction. 

AS TO COUNT #8:  The Court ordered the Defendant to serve SIX (6) months CONCURRENT to count #7 in the House of Correction with credit for 219 days time served.

The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program 
The defendant is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.

The Court advised the defendant of the determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - No controlled substances or alcohol; Absolute sobriety.
 - AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - Random urine screens to ensure compliance;
 - Seek and maintain employment and/or schooling for 40 hours a week;
 - Perform 75 hours of community service;
 - Pay restitution in the amount of $1,539.10 as follows:  $186.85 to the Crime Victim Compensation Program; $801.75 to Seth H.; $457.00 to Maria J-M.;  and $93.50 to Gabriela D-P.
 - Pay the DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements AFTER restitution is paid.  Court ordered monies taken by the Department of Correction from up to 25% of prison funds.  Balance would be then be paid while on Extended Supervision.  If not paid, balance would convert to a civil judgment. 

